#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
tokenop — the Token Op Arcade.  macOS terminal games + a Claude Code spinner companion.

While Claude Code is thinking, a hook auto-opens your chosen game in a new
Terminal.app window; when Claude finishes, the window auto-closes (no
"terminate running process?" prompt). Pick the game that pops up.

Games:    dino · snake · pong · flappy

Commands:
  tokenop                  interactive menu (or this help when piped)
  tokenop play <game>      play a game (dino|snake|pong|flappy)
  tokenop list             list games; marks the configured default
  tokenop set <game>       set the default pop-up game
  tokenop config [--show]  show resolved config + path
  tokenop enable [--mode every-prompt|session]
                          install Claude Code hooks (merge-safe)
  tokenop disable          remove tokenop hooks (other settings untouched)
  tokenop status           hooks/mode, default game, high scores, window, env
  tokenop doctor           environment checks (PASS/WARN/FAIL)
  tokenop selftest         headless logic + config + hooks self-test
  tokenop --help           this overview

Internal hook targets (invoked by Claude Code, fail-soft):
  tokenop open             open the configured pop-up (game or selector) in a new window
  tokenop close            kill the game + close its window cleanly

Env overrides (so tests never touch real files):
  TOKENOP_CONFIG_DIR        default ~/.config/tokenop        (config.json)
  TOKENOP_STATE_DIR         default ~/.local/state/tokenop   (window.id, *.pid,
                                                            highscores.json,
                                                            hook.log)
  TOKENOP_CLAUDE_SETTINGS   default ~/.claude/settings.json (enable/disable edit
                                                            this file)

Install / uninstall:
  ./install.sh            copy to ~/.local/bin, selftest, enable, status
  ./install.sh --uninstall
"""

