# Belt-and-suspenders: curses reads ESCDELAY from the environment at init time
# to decide how long to wait after a bare ESC before treating it as a literal
# Escape. The default (~1000ms) makes arrow keys (ESC-prefixed sequences) lag
# almost a full second. Set a snappy default *before* any curses init; the
# shared input-setup helper also calls curses.set_escdelay(25) at runtime.
os.environ.setdefault("ESCDELAY", "25")

HELP_OVERVIEW = __doc__


